  "description": "### Business Purpose\nThe purpose of the `MOCK_BOOKINGS` function is to simulate a dataset of hotel bookings. This function can be used for testing, development, or demonstration purposes, allowing users to work with a predefined set of booking records without needing to access a live database. It provides a way to generate sample data for analysis, reporting, or application development.\n\n### Tables Used\n- **DUMMY**: This is a special table in SAP HANA that is used to select constant values or perform operations that do not require actual data from a physical table. It serves as a placeholder for generating the mock data in this function.\n\n### Metrics\nThe function returns the following metrics related to hotel bookings:\n- **booking_id**: A unique identifier for each booking.\n- **hotel_id**: An identifier for the hotel where the booking was made.\n- **customer_id**: An identifier for the customer who made the booking.\n- **amount**: The total amount charged for the booking.\n- **booking_date**: The date when the booking was made.\n\n### Formula\nThe function does not involve complex calculations or formulas. Instead, it uses a series of `UNION ALL` statements to combine multiple rows of constant values into a single result set. Each row represents a booking with predefined values for `booking_id`, `hotel_id`, `customer_id`, `amount`, and `booking_date`.\n\n### Suggested Data Product\nA suggested data product based on this function could be a **Booking Analysis Dashboard**. This dashboard could visualize key metrics such as:\n- Total bookings over time\n- Revenue generated from bookings\n- Customer distribution by hotel\n- Booking trends by date\n\nThe mock data generated by the `MOCK_BOOKINGS` function can be used to populate this dashboard for testing and demonstration purposes, allowing stakeholders to visualize and analyze booking patterns and financial performance in a user-friendly manner."
